title: Jessica Chan, DO San Francisco
cleaned_text: Jessica Chan, DO San Francisco [Noe Valley - 24th St Office](/locations/sf/noe24th/)- [888-663-6331](tel:888-663-6331) Education: Midwestern University Sees ages 14+ Doctors of Osteopathic Medicine, or DOs, are fully licensed and board-certified physicians who practice in all areas of medicine. DOs emphasize a whole-person approach to treatment and receive extra training in the musculoskeletal system called osteopathic manipulative treatment (OMT). DOs at One Medical typically practice in the field of family medicine, geriatrics, pediatrics, or internal medicine, and may also integrate OMT. About Jessica Jessica is an osteopathic family medicine doctor with an approach that focuses on body, mind, and spirit. To help people achieve the greatest health, she strives to develop trusting relationships that will guide them in reaching their goals. She's passionate about primary care, women's health, obstetrics, osteopathic manipulative treatment, and working with patients on stress reduction. Jessica does not have training in integrative or functional medicine, or naturopathic medicine, but may recommend these services in addition to acupuncture, massage therapy, and chiropractics depending on specific patient needs. To maintain her own health, Jessica hikes, does yoga, cooks, and spends time with family and friends. She earned her doctoral degree from the Chicago College of Osteopathic Medicine at Midwestern University and completed a family medicine residency at Ventura County Medical Center. Jessica is board-certified in family medicine. Note: OMT appointments are a special type of appointment and must be booked by our admin team. Please contact the office to schedule.
